The price of cement in Kenya has been dominated by 5 top local manufacturers of cement. The newer entrants have put downward pressure on prices and limited supply. In Kenya prices of cement is based on 50kg bags and we take a look at the factory prices for the top 5 cement producers in the country The prices below are the comparison of the price of cement from the 5 top suppliers of cement in Kenya. We have reviewed the price of both 32.5 and 42.5 grade cement       Bamburi Cement was incorporated in 1951 and started production in 1954. Today their operations in Kenya include two cement plants in Mombasa and Athiriver, and concrete manufacturing (precast and readymix concrete) plants in Nairobi (Industrial Area, Athiriver and Two Rivers) and Mombasa. MCL was founded in the year 2007 to cater to the building construction segment and is one of the top quality cement manufacturers in Kenya  Savannah Cement operates a cement grinding plant with a capacity of 2.4 million tons a year located in Nairobi. It was the first company to commission a new generation cement grinding plant using the roller press technology.  The East African Portland Cement has been producing cement since 1933 National Cement Company Limited was the third major diversification and growth initiative of Devki Group. They commenced production and supply of cement in 2010 under the brand name of Simba Cement  